Stevens/Woodbridge/Madison Central/East Brunswick Here are the Red Division champs since the GMC was formed in 1986: Sayreville dethroned South Brunswick as Red Division champs. RED DIVISION CHAMPS * South Brunswick had 164 yards, including 100 rushing. * Sayreville had 312 total yards, including 244 rushing. * Sayreville leads the all-time series, 19-2. * The two teams have a combined record of 29-4 over the last three years. * The two teams split last year with South Brunswick winning in the regular season and Sayreville in the semifinals of the Central Jersey, 4 playoffs. The two cannot meet this year since they are now in different sections. * Sayreville is averaging 31.5 points per game. * Sayreville scored three different ways by four different players _ touchdown runs by Perkinson and Miller, a 58-yard kickoff return by Myles Hartsfield and an interception by Spiecker.
